00:21:51.509 --> 00:21:55.549
and were well aware of His mighty power.

00:21:55.549 --> 00:21:58.150
The nation did not need to witness another miracle

00:21:58.150 --> 00:22:00.990
to acknowledge Jehovah as the true God.

00:22:01.950 --> 00:22:05.309
Obviously, their senses had become dull,

00:22:05.309 --> 00:22:08.269
as if they had forgotten the wonderful things

00:22:08.309 --> 00:22:10.230
Jehovah had done for them.

00:22:11.430 --> 00:22:15.349
Today, we must be determined never to forget

00:22:15.349 --> 00:22:18.670
the wonderful things that Jehovah has done for us

00:22:18.670 --> 00:22:22.670
as individuals and as a people.

00:22:22.670 --> 00:22:27.109
We do well to meditate on the abundant evidence

00:22:27.109 --> 00:22:29.109
of His Godship.

00:22:29.109 --> 00:22:34.190
Finally, how does Jehovah make Himself known to us

00:22:34.190 --> 00:22:35.630
as individuals?

00:22:36.630 --> 00:22:40.309
Jehovah answered Elijah's fervent prayers

00:22:40.309 --> 00:22:43.390
for fire and rain.

00:22:44.390 --> 00:22:48.710
Jehovah continues to be the hero of prayer today.

00:22:49.589 --> 00:22:53.589
First John 514 states that no matter what we ask

00:22:53.589 --> 00:22:57.029
according to His will, He hears us.

00:22:58.349 --> 00:23:02.230
Jehovah miraculously empowered Elijah

00:23:02.269 --> 00:23:06.230
to outrun Ahab's horse-drawn chariot

00:23:06.230 --> 00:23:09.990
for a distance of 19 miles.

00:23:10.950 --> 00:23:14.109
Today, Jehovah's spirit gives us power

00:23:14.109 --> 00:23:18.769
beyond what is normal to face our challenges successfully.

00:23:19.789 --> 00:23:21.950
As the Apostle Paul wrote,

00:23:21.950 --> 00:23:25.269
as recorded at Philippians 413,

00:23:25.269 --> 00:23:29.670
for all things I have the strength through the one

00:23:29.670 --> 00:23:33.789
who gives me power.

00:23:33.789 --> 00:23:36.269
Now, the next portion of this drama

00:23:36.269 --> 00:23:41.269
is based on 1 Kings 19, 1 through 8.

00:23:43.190 --> 00:23:47.789
This account reveals a very human side of Elijah.

00:23:48.869 --> 00:23:52.670
Faced with a death threat from wicked King Jezebel,

00:23:52.670 --> 00:23:57.670
Elijah becomes frustrated and depressed.

00:23:57.670 --> 00:24:00.910
Let us listen in and see how Jehovah

00:24:00.910 --> 00:24:05.910
comes to Elijah's rescue and proves to be the true God.

00:24:18.519 --> 00:24:22.640
Then Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done

00:24:22.640 --> 00:24:25.799
and how he had killed all the prophets with the sword.

00:24:26.759 --> 00:24:29.960
At that, Jezebel sent a messenger to Elijah saying,

00:24:30.960 --> 00:24:34.319
so may that God's due to me and add to it.

00:24:34.319 --> 00:24:35.960
If by this time tomorrow,

00:24:36.000 --> 00:24:39.279
I do not make you like each one of them.

00:24:40.319 --> 00:24:42.680
At that, he became afraid.

00:24:42.680 --> 00:24:45.200
So he got up and ran for his life.

00:24:46.240 --> 00:24:49.559
He came to be a sheba which belongs to Judah

00:24:49.559 --> 00:24:52.000
and he left his attendant there.

00:24:52.000 --> 00:24:54.759
He went a day's journey into the wilderness

00:24:54.759 --> 00:24:58.079
and came and sat down under a broom tree

00:24:58.079 --> 00:25:00.920
and he asked that he might die.

00:25:00.920 --> 00:25:01.920
He said,

00:25:01.920 --> 00:25:03.720
it is enough.

00:25:03.720 --> 00:25:07.079
Now, O Jehovah, take my life away

00:25:07.079 --> 00:25:09.759
for I am no better than my forefathers.

00:25:09.759 --> 00:25:13.920
Then he laid down and fell asleep under the broom tree.

00:25:13.920 --> 00:25:17.480
But suddenly an angel touched him and said to him,

00:25:17.480 --> 00:25:19.240
get up and eat.

00:25:19.240 --> 00:25:20.720
When he looked,

00:25:20.720 --> 00:25:24.319
there at his head was a round loaf on heated stones

00:25:24.319 --> 00:25:25.480
and a jug of water.

00:25:26.759 --> 00:25:30.319
He ate and drank and laid down again.

00:25:30.319 --> 00:25:32.279
Later, the angel of Jehovah came back

00:25:32.279 --> 00:25:35.359
and touched him and said,

00:25:35.359 --> 00:25:39.839
get up and eat for the journey will be too much for you.

00:25:39.839 --> 00:25:42.599
So he got up and ate and drank

00:25:42.599 --> 00:25:45.359
and in the strength of that nourishment,

00:25:45.359 --> 00:25:48.759
he went on for 40 days and 40 nights

00:25:48.759 --> 00:25:50.559
until he reached Horeb,

00:25:50.559 --> 00:26:00.049
the mountain of the true God.

00:26:00.049 --> 00:26:05.049
Once again, our three questions find resounding answers.

00:26:06.049 --> 00:26:09.609
One, why is it foolish to give devotion

00:26:09.609 --> 00:26:12.529
to anything or anyone other than Jehovah?

00:26:13.890 --> 00:26:17.769
Even after the miracles performed on Mount Carmo,

00:26:17.769 --> 00:26:21.970
a habit Jezebel remained unrepentant.

00:26:21.970 --> 00:26:25.329
They sank into a disapproved mental state,

00:26:25.329 --> 00:26:29.009
having gone past all moral sense.

00:26:29.009 --> 00:26:32.329
This shows that a pattern of disobedience

00:26:32.329 --> 00:26:35.329
or half-hearted worship can harden us

00:26:35.329 --> 00:26:37.609
and draw us away from the true God.

00:26:38.569 --> 00:26:41.730
Two, what could interfere

00:26:41.730 --> 00:26:45.329
with our giving exclusive devotion to Jehovah?

00:26:46.369 --> 00:26:50.730
Elijah was a man with feelings like hours.

00:26:50.730 --> 00:26:54.529
He became depressed and felt like giving up.

00:26:55.529 --> 00:26:59.890
Although all of us are susceptible to negative feelings,

00:26:59.890 --> 00:27:04.890
we must not allow them to paralyze us spiritually.

00:27:04.890 --> 00:27:09.890
Three, how does Jehovah make himself known to us as individuals?

00:27:11.250 --> 00:27:14.930
The angel of Jehovah literally fed Elijah

00:27:14.930 --> 00:27:19.930
and also infused him with spiritual and emotional strength.

00:27:21.009 --> 00:27:25.170
As humans, we will experience periods of sadness

00:27:25.170 --> 00:27:27.210
and frustration.

00:27:27.210 --> 00:27:30.250
Jehovah makes himself known to us as individuals

00:27:30.250 --> 00:27:34.410
by infusing us with encouragement through his word,

00:27:34.410 --> 00:27:38.210
his Holy Spirit, and the Christian congregation.

00:27:39.170 --> 00:27:44.170
We can trust Jehovah to rescue us from the depths of despair.

00:27:46.170 --> 00:27:51.170
The Bible account of Elijah teaches us many valuable lessons.

00:27:51.210 --> 00:27:55.809
The prophets of Bale come to realize, but too late,

00:27:55.809 --> 00:27:59.289
that Jehovah is the only true God.

00:27:59.289 --> 00:28:02.089
But that lesson is only the beginning.

00:28:02.089 --> 00:28:04.009
As the only true God,

00:28:04.009 --> 00:28:09.009
Jehovah deserves and expects our exclusive devotion.

00:28:09.849 --> 00:28:14.690
Nothing should compete with our whole soul worship of Him.

00:28:14.690 --> 00:28:18.730
Moreover, He has the power and the desire

00:28:18.730 --> 00:28:21.450
to bless and protect us.

00:28:21.450 --> 00:28:23.690
As the only true God,

00:28:23.690 --> 00:28:28.690
He will be loyal to all those loyal to Him.

00:28:29.089 --> 00:28:34.089
Therefore, may each of us continue to demonstrate intense loyalty

00:28:35.809 --> 00:28:40.809
to our Heavenly Father, the only true God, Jehovah.
